{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c330d84-c7e6-4d7d-a78a-dc39f4d3e2be","content":"Set these environment variables before launching your app:\n\n```bash\n# Enable crash dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\n\n# Full dump (type 4). Options: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\n\n# Output path (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/var/dumps/coredump.%d.%t.dmp\n```\n\nMake sure the target directory exists and is writable:\n\n```bash\nsudo mkdir -p /var/dumps\nsudo chmod 1777 /var/dumps\n```\n\n**Verify the configuration:**\n\n```bash\n# 1. Confirm the vars are set\nenv | grep DOTNET_Dbg\n\n# 2. Smoke-test with a deliberate crash\ndotnet run &\nAPP_PID=$!\nkill -s SIGABRT $APP_PID   # triggers the crash dump\n\n# 3. Check the dump was written\nls -lh /var/dumps/\n```\n\n> **Note:** The older `COMPlus_Dbg*` prefix still works but `DOTNET_Dbg*` is the canonical form since .NET 6+.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d83a571d-3f18-4e15-a53c-d2bae05f52b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about configuring automatic crash dump collection for a .NET 10 CoreCLR application running on Linux. This is a knowledge question about .NET runtime configuration, not a code change task. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":380,"requestId":"6083:32FC8B:2F579A:3CF9C9:69FFE3D5"},"id":"0601e445-140d-4720-93c4-399f30062919","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:48:14.386Z","parentId":"9151bda4-6599-4cb0-a180-b94bd86de1e9"}
